The paper deals with scheduling jobs on machines communicating via a shared channel, which is a problem in distributed computing (cs.DC) and scheduling algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the impact of failures on the performance, which is a topic in fault-tolerant computing (cs.SY). The use of randomization is also discussed, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
